# Backend API Development Rules

## API Contract Preservation

- **Never modify route paths** without updating `lib/api-spec/openapi.yaml` first
- **Never change request/response shapes** without updating the OpenAPI spec and running codegen
- **Always use Zod schemas** from `@workspace/api-zod` for request/response validation
- **Preserve existing API contracts** - no breaking changes to existing endpoints

## Validation Pattern

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD - Use generated Zod schemas
import { GenerateNoteBody, GenerateNoteResponse } from "@workspace/api-zod";

router.post("/notes/generate", async (req, res) => {
  const body = GenerateNoteBody.parse(req.body);
  // ... handler logic
  const data = GenerateNoteResponse.parse({ success: true, data: {...}, error: null });
  res.json(data);
});
```

## Error Handling

- Error responses must match OpenAPI `ErrorResponse` schema: `{ success: false, error: string, messages: string[] }`
- Use appropriate HTTP status codes (404, 400, 409, 500) as defined in OpenAPI spec
- Always validate params with Zod: `const params = GetClientParams.parse(req.params);`

## Route Structure

- One router per domain (clients, notes, health)
- Export default router from each route file
- Mount routes in `src/routes/index.ts`
- Use Express 5 patterns consistently

## Response Format

All responses follow: `{ success: boolean, data: T | null, error: string | null, warnings?: string[] }`
